title: Four Vikings headed to state
text: Previous Next Four Vikings headed to state Vikings doubles team Jenna Groene, left, and Mallory Meier were regional doubles champions Friday at independence. (Special to the Courier) Posted: Tuesday, October 13, 2015 3:53 pm Four Vikings headed to state Special to the Courier winfieldcourier.com | 0 comments The Viking girls tennis team competed at the regional tournament in Independence last weekend and finished in third place. “Pretty even regional here, any three teams could have won it, came down to the last few matches and we came up a little short,” coach Brian Shaw said.
